AttributeList.Text: This network contains the acknowledgement for the safety-program. Safety could be acknowledge by the HMI or by reset buttons connected to the units. Ack_OP enables fail-safe acknowledgement from an operator control and monitoring system. Ack_GL reintegrates all passivated F-I/O modules of the calling F-Runtime group. In the basic AF, no reset buttons in the units are connected, so
Copy input tags from failsafe-input modules.

*** Safety Zone 1 - Safety Function: Emergency Stop*** This function implements a safe shutdown (STO) of drives in emergency. When the emergency button is pressed, the actuator(s) are switched off with STO. For more information, please refer to: https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/ww/en/view/109793462

*** Safety Zone 1 - Safety Function: Protective Door *** This function implements safe protective door monitoring without guard looking. The actuator(s) are switched off (STO) safely when the protective door is opend during operation or a fault is detected. For more information, please refer to: https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/ww/en/view/109793462

*** Safety Zone 1 - Safety Function: Light Curtain *** This function is not implemented. Additionally required safety functions can be implemented in accordance to the risk assessment. Application examples to commonly used safety functions can be found in SIOS and selected via Safety Select: https://support.industry.siemens.com/cs/ww/en/view/109773295

*** Safety Zone 1 - Actuators *** This network implements the interconnection to the actuator hardware. The Safety integrated functions of drives 1 to 6 are controlled via PROFIsafe with LDrvSafe function blocks.
*** Safety Zone 1 - Zone State Summary *** This network summerizes the states of the safety functions for diagnostics in the standard user program.
Summarize the Status Information from all Safety Zones and form general diagnostic bits.
Move temporary status information to data exchange DB "DataFromSafety"
